    </audio>

    <h2>History of Biryani</h2>
    <p>Biryani has a rich and flavorful history that dates back several centuries, with its origins often traced to Persian cuisine. It is believed to have been brought to the Indian subcontinent by Persian travelers and Mughal rulers, where it evolved and merged with local spices and cooking traditions. Over time, biryani became a royal dish in Mughal kitchens and spread across regions, giving rise to numerous regional variations. Each version reflects the culture, ingredients, and tastes of the area, making biryani not just a dish, but a historical journey on a plate.</p>
